This paper discusses the challenges in building explanatory artificial intelligence systems, specifically for deep neural networks, and focuses on the types of explanations that are useful for and demanded by society. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of building trust and compliance with regulatory and policy changes, which suggests relevance to the sub-categories cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CY (Cybersecurity and Privacy). Finally, the paper also touches on the topic of validation, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
